x4freetext: Typically 5 to 10 target foils of
2.5 cm diam together with pure aluminium catcher and
degrader foils were held in a water cooled target
holder and irradiated with 5-15 mu-a of helium ions
for 1 to 2 hours. The target holder acted as a
faraday cup, and the integrated beam intensity during
each bombardment was measured with a precision
current integrator.
A shielded 7.6 cm x 7.6 cm NaI(Tl) crystal
was used in conjunction with a 400 channel analyser
to measure gamma-spectra. X-ray activities were
measured  using a 0.65 cm x 5.1 cm NaI(Tl) crystal
coupled to a single channel analyser and scaler.
Results from initial energy spread plus
energy straggling in stacks.
Additional uncertainty of 10% due to
uncertainty in integrated flux and detector efficiency.
